    <div id="intro" class="fade-in">
      <div class="photo-float-right">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Saint Michael Chan with basketball and halo" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Saint Michael Chan (陳紀正) in his Durham University kit, with sacred basketball and golden halo. Official devotional portrait, c. 2024.</div>
      </div>
      <p><strong>Saint Michael Chan</strong> (Chinese: <strong>陳紀正</strong>, romanised: <em>Chan Kei Ching</em>; born <strong>8 December 2002</strong>, <a href="#">Hong Kong</a>) is a living <a href="#">Roman Catholic</a> saint, student of <a href="#">Theoretical Physics</a>, basketball captain, and spiritual figure venerated for his boundless love for humanity. He is described by those who know him as embodying <em>resilience, integrity, and knowledge</em> — and by those who have faced him on the court as simply terrifying.</p>
      <p>His theme song is <a href="#">"Like Him"</a> by Tyler the Creator. His spirit animal is the <strong>White Tiger</strong>. His go-to meal is <strong>Tesco mac and cheese (discounted)</strong>. These facts are considered equally sacred.</p>
      <p>
        <span class="tag">Living saint</span>
        <span class="tag">Durham University</span>
        <span class="tag">Hong Kong</span>
        <span class="tag">Theoretical Physics</span>
        <span class="tag">Basketball captain</span>
        <span class="tag">8 December 2002</span>
        <span class="tag">White Tiger</span>
        <span class="tag">Kanye West fan</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="early">Early life</h2>
    <div class="clearfix fade-in">
      <div class="photo-float-right">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Chan outdoors in Durham" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Chan photographed beneath what witnesses described as a providentially arranged halo of tree branches, Durham, c. 2023.</div>
      </div>
      <p>Chan Kei Ching was born on <strong>8 December 2002</strong> in Hong Kong — the Feast of the Immaculate Conception — to a family he describes simply as "lovely." He was raised in Hong Kong until 2019, after which he relocated to <a href="#">Newcastle upon Tyne</a>, England, where he spent several formative years before matriculating at Durham University in 2023.</p>
      <p>At the age of six, Chan contracted a severe illness that left his physicians baffled. He recovered overnight without medical intervention — the first of several miracles attributed to himself, by himself. Throughout primary school he was known as <em>Handsome</em> and <em>Superman</em>. In secondary school, these titles evolved to <em>Batman</em> and <em>Spiderman</em>.</p>
      <p>His biggest flex, by his own account, is simply being alive. His family is his foundation. His Tesco mac and cheese is his sustenance. These things are not in conflict.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="education">Education and academic life</h2>
    <div class="clearfix fade-in">
      <p>Chan is currently in his <strong>third year</strong> of a degree in <strong>Theoretical Physics</strong> at <a href="#">Durham University</a>, St Aidan's College. The decision to study Theoretical Physics — a discipline requiring the highest order of mathematical and conceptual reasoning — has been described by peers as "very on brand for someone with a 100% shot percentage."</p>
      <p>His academic record includes the now-legendary <em>Twelve-Hour Lab Report Miracle</em> of 2023, in which he completed, submitted, and passed a laboratory report in a single sitting with no sleep, minimal sustenance, and what onlookers described as "an almost eerie calm." The event has since been formally recognised by the Diocese.</p>
      <p>Life at St Aidan's College has been characterised by deep friendships, an exceptional college bar crawl culture, and one notable visit from the police at <strong>3am</strong>, the details of which Chan declines to elaborate on, and which the Church has classified as <em>under seal of confession</em>.</p>
      <blockquote>"The police knocked on my door at 3am. I answered. We did not become friends." <br><small>— Chan, recounting the incident with characteristic understatement</small></blockquote>
    </div>

    <h2 id="basketball">Basketball ministry</h2>
    <div class="clearfix fade-in">
      <div class="photo-float-left">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Saint Michael Chan holding basketball" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Chan displaying his signature one-handed basketball hold. Durham University, c. 2024. The ball, per sacred teaching, does not lie.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-float-right">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Chan in action for St Aidan's" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Chan in action for St Aidan's College. Witnesses reported he dunked on a 7-foot man shortly after this photograph was taken. The 7-foot man has not recovered spiritually.</div>
      </div>
      <p>Chan has served as <strong>Team Captain of Durham University Men's Basketball 3rd Team</strong> since 2024. Under his captaincy, the team achieved <strong>6 wins and 4 losses</strong> in the current season, following a <strong>7 wins and 3 losses</strong> record the previous year — statistics his devotees attribute to divine intervention and his rivals attribute to luck, incorrectly.</p>
      <p>His signature move is the <strong>Defence and Hustle Chant</strong> — a vocal technique in which Chan shouts the team chant so ferociously that the entire team receives a <strong>333% advantage in defensive intensity</strong>. Scientists at Durham's Physics department have been unable to explain this. Chan has noted that this is consistent with his degree.</p>
      <p>In what is now referred to simply as <em>The Dunk</em>, Chan dunked on a 7-foot African man for a buzzer beater during a competitive fixture. The man was 7 feet tall. Chan dunked on him anyway. Witnesses wept. The ball went in.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="clearfix fade-in">
      <div class="photo-float-right">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Chan holding trophy" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Chan holding a tournament trophy, Durham, c. 2023. The Rolling Stones t-shirt is confirmed sacred. The smirk is not performed.</div>
      </div>
      <p>The pinnacle of Chan's basketball career to date is the <strong>York Varsity Game</strong>, in which St Aidan's faced opponents who — in a development that transcended the sport entirely — had not brought their kit. The opposing team played without proper uniforms. Chan led his team to victory. "It was more than basketball," he later reflected, staring into the middle distance.</p>
      <p>Chan has <strong>never missed a shot</strong> in competitive play. His lifetime shooting percentage is 100%. This has been independently verified by the Church, three teammates, and the 7-foot man, who confirmed it while staring at the ceiling.</p>
      <h3>The rival: Daniel Chan</h3>
      <p>Chan's primary rival is a figure known only as <strong>Daniel Chan</strong>, whom Chan has publicly described as "a dickhead." The Diocese has chosen not to investigate this claim. Historians note that even saints have rivals, and that Chan's assessment is presented here without editorial comment, as a matter of sacred record.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="faith">Faith and devotion</h2>
    <div class="clearfix fade-in">
      <div class="photo-float-right">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Chan in goat pen" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Chan during a pilgrimage to a pygmy goat enclosure, Durham, c. 2023. Theologians note the parallel with the biblical shepherd tradition. Chan has said nothing about this visit. He did not need to.</div>
      </div>
      <p>Chan describes his faith as rooted in a single, radical ambition: to turn hate into love. "If I could perform one more miracle," he has said, "I hope I could solve all the conflicts as soon as I arrive. I turn the hate into love. Make love." The Vatican has noted this statement as theologically sound and also simply correct.</p>
      <p>He is a devoted <strong>dog person</strong>, a night owl by nature, and a man who thanks God every evening at dinner — a ritual so consistent it has been designated his official Feast Day, observed nightly, wherever food is present. He is also a committed <strong>Kanye West fan</strong> and a vocal opponent of Taylor Swift, a position he holds with the same conviction as his other theological stances.</p>
      <p>People are invited to pray to Saint Michael Chan for <em>love, the removal of hate, and anything good overall and eventually</em>. The scope of his patronage is intentionally broad. He wants to help. He is also open to basketball-related petitions.</p>
      <p>Chan's most sacred act of humility occurred in Newcastle, when he walked an entire street without realising he was not wearing trousers — nor underwear. The incident disturbed many bystanders, but Chan, upon reflection, interpreted it as a lesson in vulnerability and the dangers of being a night owl who dresses in a hurry. The Church has classified this as <em>The Naked Revelation</em>.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="miracles">Miracles</h2>
    <div class="fade-in">
      <div class="miracle-box">
        <div class="miracle-label">First miracle — self-healing, c. 2008</div>
        <h3>The Overnight Recovery of Hong Kong</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">At the age of six, Chan fell gravely ill. His family prayed. By morning he had recovered entirely, with no medical explanation. Church authorities accepted this as the First Miracle — uniquely, an act of self-intercession. Precedent: none.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="miracle-box">
        <div class="miracle-label">Second miracle — academic endurance, c. 2023</div>
        <h3>The Twelve-Hour Lab Report</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">Chan completed an entire laboratory report in twelve hours, submitted it on time, and passed the examination. Witnesses confirmed he consumed only modest provisions. The Diocese confirmed this as the Second Miracle. Durham Physics department confirmed it was "a solid report, actually."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="miracle-box">
        <div class="miracle-label">Third miracle — 100% shot percentage</div>
        <h3>The Infallible Shot</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">Chan has never missed a shot in competitive play. Ever. In any game. His shooting percentage across all recorded fixtures is 100%. Statisticians have described this as impossible. Chan has described this as Tuesday.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="miracle-box">
        <div class="miracle-label">Fourth miracle — attributed intercession</div>
        <h3>The Eternal Sleep of the Sleepless Man</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">A man who had not slept for three days prayed to Saint Michael Chan and immediately fell into the most peaceful sleep of his life. He has not been seen awake since. The Church classified this as a miracle of <em>absolute rest</em>. His family report he appears content.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="miracle-box">
        <div class="miracle-label">Fifth miracle — collegiate gastronomy, c. 2022</div>
        <h3>The 17 Pints and the Victory Poop of St Mary's Garden</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">During a legendary college bar crawl, Chan consumed 17 pints across multiple venues — a feat that by all physiological standards should have been impossible — before making his way to St Mary's College and depositing what witnesses described as "a victory" in their garden. Chan survived. St Mary's garden has since been blessed, whether they wanted it to be or not. The Church has classified this as a miracle of <em>extraordinary endurance and territorial marking</em>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 id="iconography">Iconography</h2>
    <div class="clearfix fade-in">
      <div class="photo-float-left">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Devotional portrait 2" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Second devotional portrait — classical blessing pose. Art historians describe the physique as "frankly impressive." The Vatican described it as "noted."</div>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-float-right">
        <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Devotional portrait 3" />
        <div class="photo-caption">Third devotional portrait — traditional robes in the manner of Christ Pantocrator. The red garment represents sacrifice, Durham purple, and the warmth of a man who eats discounted mac and cheese by choice.</div>
      </div>
      <p>Saint Michael Chan has produced an unusually rich body of devotional iconography for a living saint. Three formal altarpiece portraits have been commissioned, each featuring a golden halo, the distinctive arched altarpiece frame, and an expression of serene, slightly intimidating holiness that art historians at Durham have described as "entirely earned."</p>
      <p>A fourth image — the so-called <em>Tongue Revelation</em> — remains under active theological debate at Durham's Faculty of Divinity. Its significance is unclear. Its impact on viewers is not.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="timeline">Timeline of a living saint</h2>
    <div class="fade-in">
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">8 December 2002</div>
          <div class="timeline-text">Born in Hong Kong on the Feast of the Immaculate Conception. The timing is noted. The halo was not yet visible but was understood to be present.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">c. 2008</div>
          <div class="timeline-text">Falls gravely ill. Recovers overnight without medical explanation. Performs his first miracle on himself. Sets a precedent that has not been repeated in the history of the Church.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
          <div class="timeline-year">2008–2019</div>
          <div class="timeline-text">Primary and secondary school in Hong Kong. Accumulates titles: Handsome, Superman, Batman, Spiderman. Does not miss a single shot. Befriends everyone. Annoys Daniel Chan.</div>
