    <h2 id="legacy">Legacy and veneration</h2>
    <div class="fade-in">
      <p>Chan is venerated at St Aidan's College, Durham University, where he is known as <em>One Punch Man</em>. His feast day is celebrated every evening at dinner. He is the only saint in recorded history whose feast day is daily, always involves food, and has never once been cancelled due to weather, exams, or the 3am police visit.</p>
      <p>His three altarpiece portraits circulate widely online. His quote about the anus hair has been shared more times than any theological text produced at Durham in the last decade. His 100% shot percentage has never been disputed. His rivalry with Daniel Chan continues.</p>
      <p>His greatest miracle, by his own account, remains simply this: he is alive. He lives with people he loves. He wants to make love from hate. He eats Tesco mac and cheese. He listens to Tyler the Creator. He is, by every available measure, exactly the saint the world needs right now.</p>
    </div>

